# Tailwind CSS v4 Styling Guide

## Configuration

This project uses **Tailwind CSS v4** with CSS-first configuration. There is NO `tailwind.config.ts` file.

- All design tokens are defined in `src/index.css` via the `@theme` directive
- The Vite plugin `@tailwindcss/vite` handles processing
- Colors use the **OKLCH** color space for perceptual uniformity

## Design Tokens

Use these semantic color tokens (not raw colors):

| Token                    | Usage                                |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------ |
| `bg-background`          | Page background                      |
| `text-foreground`        | Primary text                         |
| `bg-card` / `text-card-foreground` | Card surfaces              |
| `bg-primary` / `text-primary-foreground` | Primary buttons, links |
| `bg-secondary`           | Secondary buttons, subtle backgrounds|
| `bg-destructive`         | Delete buttons, error states         |
| `bg-muted` / `text-muted-foreground` | Disabled, subtle text     |
| `bg-accent`              | Hover states, highlights             |
| `border-border`          | Default borders                      |
| `ring-ring`              | Focus rings                          |
| `bg-sidebar`             | Sidebar background                   |

## Dark Mode

- Dark mode is toggled via `.dark` class on `<html>`
- Managed by `useThemeStore` (persisted to localStorage)
- Dark overrides are defined in `src/index.css` under `.dark { ... }`
- **Never use** `dark:` variant in component code — the CSS variables handle it automatically

## Class Merging

Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils.ts` to merge Tailwind classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils.ts';

<div className={cn('base-classes', isActive && 'active-classes', className)} />
```

This correctly handles Tailwind class conflicts (e.g., `p-2` vs `p-4`).

## Responsive Design

Use Tailwind's mobile-first breakpoints:

```tsx
<div className="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
```

Standard breakpoints: `sm` (640px), `md` (768px), `lg` (1024px), `xl` (1280px).

## Typography

- Font family: Inter (sans), JetBrains Mono (mono) — defined in `@theme`
- Use Tailwind's `text-*` utilities for sizing — **minimum `text-xs` (12px) for readable UI copy**; do not use arbitrary sizes below 12px (e.g. `text-[0.6875rem]`) for labels, hints, or body text on product surfaces
- **Surface pairing:** on `bg-card` / `bg-popover`, use `text-card-foreground` (or shadcn `Card`, which sets it). On `bg-background`, use `text-foreground`. Never put `text-foreground` on a card surface without checking contrast in both modes
- **Preset axes:** type scale, density, and motion floors — `docs/reference/preset-product-design-rules.md`
- Heading pattern: `text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground`
- Body pattern: `text-sm text-muted-foreground`

## Spacing Conventions

- Page padding: `p-6`
- Section gaps: `space-y-6` or `space-y-8`
- Card internal padding: handled by shadcn Card components
- Grid gaps: `gap-4` (standard), `gap-6` (sections)

## Component Styling with CVA

Use `class-variance-authority` for components with variants:

```tsx
const variants = cva('base', {
  variants: {
    variant: { default: '...', destructive: '...' },
    size: { sm: '...', default: '...', lg: '...' },
  },
  defaultVariants: { variant: 'default', size: 'default' },
});
```

## shadcn/ui Components

All shadcn/ui primitives live in `src/shared/components/ui/`. When adding new components via the shadcn CLI, they will be placed there automatically (configured in `components.json`).

## Forbidden Patterns

- Never use inline `style={}` attributes
- Never use `@apply` in component files (only in `index.css` base layer)
- Never use `dark:` variant in components — rely on CSS variable overrides
- Never hardcode colors — always use design tokens
- Never use `!important`
- **Never fade page/route content with opacity** — `--animate-fade-in-up` maps to transform-only `route-rise` in `index.css`. Do not reintroduce `opacity: 0` on `PageTransition`, layout outlets, or other wrappers that hold primary copy (causes invisible text with `animation-fill-mode: both` + reduced motion). Opacity fades are OK on overlays/dialogs, not on main content shells
